<HEADLINE>
FT  06 JUL 94 / Cathedral Employment in liquidation
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Cathedral Employment Enterprise, one of the biggest providers of training
for the unemployed in London, yesterday went into voluntary liquidation with
debts of nearly Pounds 1m. The joint liquidators said the chance of selling
the whole concern was limited but constituent parts might be sold. Cathedral
employed about 150 staff in 50 centres across London. Its annual turnover
was Pounds 3m.
