<HEADLINE>
FT  06 JUL 94 / Accidents decline in farming
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The number of people killed in accidents at work in farming and forestry
last year was the lowest recorded, the Health and Safety Executive announced
yesterday.
Forty-one people died in such accidents, 11 fewer than in 1992. The average
for the previous seven years was 60.
According to the HSE's economic advisers unit about 40 per cent of accidents
at work in farming, forestry and fisheries could be prevented if more care
was taken. The costs of these accidents are at least Pounds 325m a year, it
added.
</TEXT>
