<HEADLINE>
FT  06 JUL 94 / World Cup '94: Bulgaria beat Mexico in penalty shoot-out
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Bulgaria are through to the quarter-finals for the first time in their
history after beating Mexico in a penalty shoot-out at Giants Stadium, New
Jersey, yesterday.
The game finished 1-1 after 30 goalless minutes of extra time.
Bulgarian striker Stoichkov gave his side the lead with an unstoppable
left-foot shot in the 7th minute only for Mexico to equalise within 11
minutes. Kremenliev was adjudged to have fouled Alves in the penalty area,
allowing Alberto Garcia the chance to score from the penalty spot.
The match was halted for over five minutes midway through the half when
Mexican defender Bernal became tangled in his own net, damaging the support.
In the second half, Kremenliev and Mexico's Luis Garcia were both sent off
for second bookable offences as the game drifted towards extra time.
The first three penalties were missed, but then Guentchev, Borimirov and
Letchkov scored for Bulgaria and only Suarez hit the target for the
Mexicans.
Bulgaria now play Germany on Sunday.
</TEXT>
