FT  06 JUL 94 / Hunt urges unions to end Labour link
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Unions should come out of opposition by seeking partnerships in the
workplace and by cutting their 'discredited' link with the Labour party,
employment secretary David Hunt told a Trades Union Congress conference on
jobs yesterday.
Mr Hunt (pictured giving his speech) is the first Tory cabinet min-ister to
attend a TUC conference for more than a decade. He had been heckled outside
Congress House in London but received polite applause at the end of his
speech.
Mr Hunt also said that some unemployed people needed to change their
attitude to the new service-sector jobs.
Speakers at the conference, who included Mr John Prescott, shadow employment
secretary, Mr Howard Davies, CBI director-general, and Mr John Monks, TUC
general secretary, backed the goal of full employment but differed over the
means of achieving it.
