<HEADLINE>
FT  05 JUL 94 / Signalmen's union discusses options
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Leaders of the RMT transport union were discussing their next move in the
railway signal dispute last night.
The 21-strong executive was deciding whether to escalate the conflict by
extending the 24-hour weekly stoppages to two days a week. It was also
looking at Railtrack's latest pay proposal that would give most signalmen
self-financing pay increases of between 13 per cent and 26 per cent.
There seems little likelihood, however, that tomorrow's 24-hour strike can
be avoided.
