<HEADLINE>
FT  05 JUL 94 / World Trade News: Court victory for P&amp;O
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOHN BARHAM
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   BUENOS AIRES
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
A consortium led by P&amp;O of the UK has won the first round in a court battle
to win control of two terminals in the port of Buenos Aires, writes John
Barham in Buenos Aires.
In June the government cancelled P&amp;O's offer to manage the two terminals as
a 25 year concession despite having made the highest bid. However, a Buenos
Aires federal judge ruled that P&amp;O's local ally Port Investments did meet
bidding terms.
