<HEADLINE>
FT  05 JUL 94 / World Stock Markets: Rolimpex offer returns to original
price
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHRISTOPHER BOBINSKI
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   WARSAW
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Yesterday saw the public offer of 50 per cent of the equity in Rolimpex, the
state-owned agricultural goods import and export company, open at the
original minimum price of 300,000 zlotys per share, in spite of earlier
statements by the Privatisation Ministry that the price would be reduced to
take in the market downturn, writes Christopher Bobinski in Warsaw.
Defending this, Mr Wieslaw Kaczmarek, the minister, said: 'It is not my
intention to contribute to the fall in prices by dropping the Rolimpex price
 -it is a first rate company.'
Yesterday also saw the first market quotation of shares in the recently
privatised Jelfa pharmaceuticals group, which fell 7 per cent from the
initial public offer price of 300,000.
Equities staged a rebound after the recent correction, but light volume and
moderate price movements were seen as signals that the market had not
recovered confidence after more than three months of bearish trade. The Wig
index rose 226.5, or 2.9 per cent, to 8,019.0 in turnover that fell 7.5 per
cent to 509bn zlotys.
