   By BERNARD SIMON
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   TORONTO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Mr Paul Reichmann's efforts to resurrect his family's property empire took
another step forward with the appointment of two experienced executives to
senior posts in recently-formed Reichmann companies.
Mr Evan Marks, a close adviser to financier Mr George Soros, has been named
chief executive of Reichmann International, the New York-based partnership
between Mr Soros and the Reichmann family. Reichmann International acts as
an adviser to Mr Soros's Quantum Realty Fund.
Mr Vernon Schwartz, former president of Catellus Development, a large
