<HEADLINE>
FT  05 JUL 94 / International Company News: Dwyer Estates back in black with
Pounds 0.38m
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Dwyer Estates, the Irish property investment and trading group, returned to
the black in the six months to March 31 with a pre-tax profit of Pounds
378,000, against a loss of Pounds 729,000.
The recovery was achieved on turnover down from Pounds 2.82m to Pounds 2.43m
and struck after a cut in interest payable from Pounds 2.06m to Pounds
965,000 and a reduction of realised deficit on sale of properties from
Pounds 537,000 to Pounds 37,000.
Earnings per share emerged at 0.99p (2.69p losses).
Directors said that following December's rights issue, which increased net
worth by Pounds 12.3m, net assets at end-March were Pounds 26.7m - 52p a
share - and net debt stood at Pounds 29.8m.
</TEXT>
