<HEADLINE>
FT  05 JUL 94 / UK Company News: CE Heath to sell Australian offshoot
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
CE Heath, the insurance broker, has reached a conditional agreement to sell
its underwriting subsidiary, Heath Australia, for ADollars 1m (Pounds
400,000) after increasing reserves against further losses by more than
Pounds 8m.
The deal is designed to draw a line under the losses from Australian
underwriting operations which have marred results recently.
It will reduce pre-tax profits for the year to March 31 1994 to Pounds
3.84m, compared with a preliminary figure announced last month of Pounds
11.8m.
But Mr Peter Presland, chief executive, said 'shareholders will be far
better served by the elimination of any further exposure to losses. The
additional exceptional loss of Pounds 8m is considered to be a a worthwhile
cost of achieving certainty.'
Heath Australia, which is no longer underwriting new business, is to be
acquired by CE Heath International Holdings, an independently listed group
in which Heath owns a 23 per cent stake.
</TEXT>
