<HEADLINE>
FT  05 JUL 94 / Observer: Snakes 'n' ladders
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
KPMG Career Consultancy Services is holding a career management day today,
where some of its neat little gadgets will be on display. When the firm goes
along to see prospective clients these days, it whips out its collection of
brain teasers, or mind twisters as they are known in the US.
The puzzles include a 'three-card trick'; 'clip-the-queen'; the 'stubborn
pencil'; and a miniature treasure chest from which you must extract a
playing card without breaking the seal.
'It's a marketing tool with a psychological edge, which is designed to show
the creativity of the KPMG approach,' says a staffer. Given some of the
twisted minds populating the marketing world, mind twisters seem an entirely
appropriate way of getting a foot in the door.
</TEXT>
