<HEADLINE>
FT  05 JUL 94 / World Trade News: Rolls-Royce plant order
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANDREW BAXTER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Rolls-Royce, the UK aero-engine and power equipment group, has won its first
full turnkey power station order in Indonesia through a Pounds 60m contract
from PLN, the national electricity utility, writes Andrew Baxter.
The UK company will supply all the electromechanical equipment and handle
civil works for a 60MW combined cycle power station at Samarinda in East
Kalimantan.
