<HEADLINE>
FT  05 JUL 94 / Warrants issued in for Venezuelan drug firm executives
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOSEPH MANN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
A criminal court judge has issued arrest warrants against executives at
eight pharmaceutical companies in Venezuela for alleged fraud in product
pricing, writes Joseph Mann.
Executives, some of them foreigners, from subsidiaries of four international
companies, Ciba-Geigy, Rhone-Poulenc, Sandoz and Servier, were among those
cited. According to Judge Cristobal Ramirez, the eight companies supplied
'padded' price lists when the previous administration was preparing price
controls.
One drug company executive said the judge's decision was based on a
'misunderstanding' and could be clarified. News of the warrants came as the
government seeks to convince private companies they should feel confident
about investing in Venezuela.
</TEXT>
