FT  05 JUL 94 / Communists back Kuchma
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JILL BARSHAY
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   KIEV
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Ukraine's Communist party said it would back Mr Leonid Kuchma, a former
prime minister, in the race for the presidency against Mr Leonid Kravchuk,
the incumbent. The party's support could be crucial in the run-off poll on
Sunday. Mr Kuchma trailed Mr Kravchuk by only 6.5 percentage points in the
first round last month , when the Communist vote gave 13 points to another
Socialist candidate. Mr Kuchma favours closer relations with Russia while
his rival appeals to more nationalist sentiment in the country. Ukraine's
Communists are the single largest bloc in parliament and have attracted
enough independents to create a clear legislative majority. 'The Communists
are the only well-organised political party in Ukraine,' said a western
diplomat. 'Their support could be a significant factor.'
